"CI/CD Pipeline Using Jenkins, Ansible, Docker, and GitHub on AWS"

Project Overview:
This project demonstrates a fully automated CI/CD pipeline implementation using Jenkins multibranch pipelines, Ansible for configuration management, GitHub as source control, and Docker for production deployments â€” all hosted on AWS EC2 instance

---

Tools:
- Jenkins (Multibranch Pipeline)
- Ansible (Server provisioning)
- GitHub (Source Code Management)
- Docker (Containerization)
- AWS EC2 (Infrastructure)
- Groovy (Jenkinsfile)
- Linux (Ubuntu)

---

Architecture:
- Jenkins Master Node** on `t2.large` EC2 instance  
- Test Node** (for develop branch) on `t2.micro`  
- Production Node** (for master branch) on `t2.micro`  
- Docker runs only on the **prod node**  
- Ansible used to install required software (Java, Docker, Jenkins)
